<HL> Suffield Financial Corp. Holders Plan to Discuss Buying Coastal Unit </HL>
<SO> </SO>
<CO> SFCP </CO>
<IN> TNM </IN>
<DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two men who own 9.98% of the shares outstanding of Suffield Financial Corp. said they plan to discuss with management acquiring Suffield's Coastal Savings Bank susbidiary. 

   Milo L. Pike, president of Pike Industries Inc., Tilton, N.H., and Henry M. Powers, chairman of C.H. Sprague &amp; Son Co., Portsmouth, N.H., disclosed the plan in a Securities and Exchange Commission filing. 
They said they may sell the subsidiary, based in Portland, Maine, after buying it. 

   In Suffield, Conn., a spokeswoman for Suffield Financial said the bank holding company didn't have any immediate comment. 

   Messrs. 
Pike and Powers reiterated a previous statement that they are looking for a third party to acquire Suffield. 
Mr. Pike has been an active investor in New England bank stocks. 

</TEXT>
